{
  "text": "Theorem A. Let A be a noetherian ring and let M be a finitely generated A-module. The Rees algebra R(M ) of M , as defined in [CITATION_1] , is equal to the image of the canonical map",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "11596298"
